# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Environment variables template.
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file to `.env.local` in the same `web/` folder:  cp .env.example .env.local
#   2. Fill in the real values on the right of each `=` (no quotes, no spaces around `=`).
#   3. Restart the dev server (`npm run dev`) so Next.js picks the values up.
#
# `.env.local` is gitignored and must NEVER be committed — it holds real secrets.
# This `.env.example` carries NO real values and IS committed, so the next person
# knows which variables to set.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Moralis API key — powers wallet-tracker token detail on BNB Chain & Avalanche
# (chains with no keyless token source). Free tier is enough.
# Get one at: https://admin.moralis.io  → create a project → copy the API key.
# Server-side only; never exposed to the browser. If unset, those two chains show
# balance only (no token breakdown) — nothing else breaks.
MORALIS_API_KEY=

# ── Optional: only needed for the Supabase keep-alive cron (see ARCHITECTURE.md) ──
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# CRON_SECRET=
